{
  "suites": {
    "title_fr": "Suites numériques",
    "icon": "timeline",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Rappel",
        "content": [
          "Une suite $(u_n)$ est croissante si $u_{n+1} \\ge u_n$, décroissante si $u_{n+1} \\le u_n$.",
          "Suite arithmétique : $u_{n+1} = u_n + r$, $u_n = u_0 + nr$, $S_n = \\frac{(n+1)(u_0+u_n)}{2}$.",
          "Suite géométrique : $u_{n+1} = q u_n$, $u_n = u_0 q^n$, $S_n = u_0 \\frac{1-q^{n+1}}{1-q}$.",
          "Suite arithmético-géométrique : $u_{n+1} = a u_n + b$. Si $a \\ne 1$, point fixe $\\ell = \\frac{b}{1-a}$, poser $v_n = u_n - \\ell$ (géométrique de raison $a$)."
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "Moyenne de Césaro",
        "content": [
          "Si $\\lim_{n\\to+\\infty} u_n = \\ell$ alors $\\lim_{n\\to+\\infty} \\frac{u_1+\\ldots+u_n}{n} = \\ell$.",
          "Si $\\lim_{n\\to+\\infty} (u_{n+1} - u_n) = \\ell$ alors $\\lim_{n\\to+\\infty} \\frac{u_n}{n} = \\ell$."
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "Règle d'Alembert",
        "content": [
          "Soit $(u_n)$ une suite positive. Si $\\lim \\frac{u_{n+1}}{u_n} = \\ell$ :",
          "Si $\\ell < 1$ alors $\\lim u_n = 0$.",
          "Si $\\ell > 1$ alors $\\lim u_n = +\\infty$."
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "Symbole somme et produit",
        "content": [
          "$\\sum_{k=1}^n k = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2}$, $\\sum_{k=1}^n k^2 = \\frac{n(n+1)(2n+1)}{6}$",
          "$\\sum_{k=0}^n q^k = \\frac{1-q^{n+1}}{1-q}$",
          "$\\sum_{k=0}^n C_n^k = 2^n$, $\\sum_{k=0}^n k C_n^k = n 2^{n-1}$"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
